# python-build definition for mise's CORE `python` tool
# =====================================================================
# This makes the prebuilt tarball published by this repo selectable as a
# *version* of mise's core `python` tool (pyenv/python-build under the hood),
# NOT as a separate `http:` tool. `python@3.6.15` then coexists with the
# precompiled 3.11 / 3.14 as ONE python tool.
#
# THE FILENAME IS THE VERSION STRING.
#   python-build resolves `python@3.6.15` to a definition file literally named
#   `3.6.15`. Rename this file and the version changes — keep them equal.
#
# "copy" BUILD MODE = NO COMPILE.
#   `install_package ... "copy"` downloads the tarball and copies it in AS-IS
#   (this is the GraalPy / prebuilt pattern). No ./configure, no make. The
#   tarball root must contain bin/ lib/ ... directly, which our packaging step
#   guarantees (tar -C <prefix> .).
#
# WHERE THIS MUST LIVE TO BE PICKED UP.
#   The directory holding this file must be on PYTHON_BUILD_DEFINITIONS, and it
#   must be OUTSIDE mise's cache (which `mise cache clear` wipes). Install with
#   compile mode scoped to ONLY that one command (see README.md):
#     MISE_PYTHON_COMPILE=1 \
#     PYTHON_BUILD_DEFINITIONS=~/.config/mise/python-build-defs \
#     mise install python@3.6.15
#
# PLACEHOLDERS to fill in after the first release exists:
#   <OWNER>   GitHub org/user that hosts this python-builds repo.
#   <SHA256>  sha256 of the tarball, taken from the release's `<asset>.sha256`
#             sidecar (the `#<sha>` fragment makes python-build verify it).
#
# The URL + asset name below MUST match the workflow's published asset EXACTLY:
#   tag    cpython-v3.6.15
#   asset  cpython-3.6.15-aarch64-apple-darwin.tar.gz
install_package "cpython-3.6.15-custom" \
  "https://github.com/<OWNER>/python-builds/releases/download/cpython-v3.6.15/cpython-3.6.15-aarch64-apple-darwin.tar.gz#<SHA256>" \
  "copy"
